	<key>NSCameraUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop uses your camera to scan supplement and medication labels for instant identification and health insights.</string>
	<key>NSMicrophoneUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop uses your microphone for voice capture so you can log supplements, create tasks, and talk to AI hands-free.</string>
	<key>NSSpeechRecognitionUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop uses speech recognition to transcribe your voice into text for quick logging and AI commands.</string>
	<key>NSHealthShareUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop reads heart rate, sleep, steps, and other health data from Apple Health to give you a complete picture alongside your ring data.</string>
	<key>NSHealthUpdateUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop can write workouts and health metrics you log to Apple Health so all your apps stay in sync.</string>
	<key>NSLocationWhenInUseUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop uses your location to map your outdoor walks, runs, and rides and measure distance during a workout.</string>
	<key>NSLocationAlwaysAndWhenInUseUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop uses your location in the background so it can keep recording your route and distance while a workout is active and the screen is off.</string>
	<key>NSBluetoothAlwaysUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop connects to your smart ring over Bluetooth to read heart rate, SpO₂, sleep, and activity data.</string>
	<key>NSCalendarsUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop reads your calendar events so the assistant can plan your day around them. It never changes events without your confirmation.</string>
	<key>NSCalendarsFullAccessUsageDescription</key>
	<string>PulseLoop reads your calendar events so the assistant can plan your day around them. It never changes events without your confirmation.</string>
